4. Bidirectional vs Unidirectional Relationships

Unidirectional:
Only one entity knows about the relationship.

@OneToMany
private List<Post> posts;

Bidirectional:
Both entities reference each other.

// In User
@OneToMany(mappedBy = "user")
private List<Post> posts;

// In Post
@ManyToOne
@JoinColumn(name = "user_id")
private User user;

Best Practice:
Use bidirectional relationships when you need to navigate from both sides. Always set the
mappedBy attribute on the non-owning side.

